<br>
Funny, as I'm reading through this post, I'm recalling a long conversation myself and a couple of buddies from work had last night.<br>
<br>
We were discussing the ways of dealing with terrorism, of dealing with Saddam Cumstain, and generally speaking, the ways we could deal with any of those &quot;Countries&quot; that don't like us. (I use quotations around this word, because without the United States, most of these people would either have no home, or would be rampantly anarchist.) <br>
<br>
My standing on this topic is, that while war is effective, it costs the US more time, money and human life than the people against whom we are warring. The US is notorious for blowing up a country, or being involved in the blowing up of a country, then being the only souls in the &quot;International Community&quot; to help with the efforts of rebuilding. The French, who apparently hate us so much, owe us much for the rebuilding after WWII (And, we didn't blow them up, the Germans did) the German people owe us their entire country, most of the Middle East, at some point, has received mass efforts of aid, and assistance from the US. <br>
<br>
Funny how easily forgotten these things are, after only a generation or two. Funny how the very peoples that we gave aid, assistance, or in some cases, LIBERTY, hate us so. Funny how the United States leftist regime focuses not on these things, but seeks to build internal strife by accusing the government (only while there's a Republican president, mind you) of being hate/war mongers.<br>
<br>
Well.. Let me be president for one year. Please. I would only do one thing. No wars, no major economic changes, no radical right wing policy. I would cut off ALL foreign aid, I would close down the American borders entirely. Nothing coming in or out for one year. The United States is self-sufficient.. How many other countries out there are? How many of these people that hate us would cry in their Budweisers when we don't let their immigrants in, or send them medical aid? How much hate for an American Empire would there be, when we quit rebuilding cities in other countries after earthquakes?<br>
<br>
I don't like this American hate. I think it's unwarranted, and from those within our own borders, it's disgustingly left wing, and entirely argumentative. <br>
<br>
In closing, try to open your eyes to the good things the United States does. Ask yourself, &quot;How many other nations offered the US aid when downtown Fort Worth was blown apart by a tornado? How many other countries offered the US aid when wildfires and mudslides defaced most of California?&quot;  When you come up with the correct answer to these questions, (It's zero, to the slow among you) think a little harder about criticizing America's &quot;Evil Empire&quot; foreign policy.<br>
<br>
